{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"IMPLEMENTATION KICKOFF + plan-review advisory triage (2026-06-30, worktree code-review-capability, local build).\n\nEarned a fresh certified plan-review attestation (verdict PASS, 0 blocking, 20 advisory; model=opus-4-8 verifier=sonnet-4-6; signed key_id 412fa5372ad877e0 over head 66f0220d7) and claimed the epic to begin implementing WS1-WS5 (the capability; WS6 stays gated on d251).\n\nAdvisory disposition — the epic is a container; nearly all 20 advisories target CHILD-STORY implementation detail and will be genuinely resolved + re-plan-reviewed when each child is claimed/implemented:\n- Overlay enum vocabulary not enumerated (A6,A17) -> WS1 defines OVERLAY_IDS + base prompt enumerates them.\n- Overlay batch-step failure fallback unspecified (A11) -> resolve in WS3 (failed overlay -> empty findings + coverage-gap note, never auto-BLOCK; recall-side).\n- WS5 abstain->BLOCK bridge two-option fork left open (A2,A3) -> pick + test ONE concrete path in WS5.\n- WS2<->WS5 shared criterion-key names not pinned (A7) -> pin exact key names as a cross-story contract in WS2, WS5 flips those same keys.\n- gitleaks/semgrep SARIF backend = NEW Engine-B code vs epic 'no core-engine change' claim (A1,A4,A12) -> the 'no change' claim is about the WORKFLOW engine; Engine B gains a SARIF-ingest backend. Reconcile wording in WS5.\n- semgrep ruleset 'subset' + licensing underspecified (A5,A8) -> WS5 names a concrete rule-selection criterion + vendoring/licensing posture.\n- Fail-closed split deserves its own ADR (A10) -> add ADR in WS5 (separate from WS4's single-pass-retirement ADR).\n- WS6 adapter ctx-constructibility + rollback test (A9,A18) -> WS6 (gated on d251).\n- Sequencing: kernel integration only validated at WS3/WS4 (A16) -> accepted; the WS boundaries are the contract seams.\n- Cap N=3 calibration (A20) -> already documented as deferred.\nEPIC-TEXT items to verify/fix during WS5: A14/A15 (epic says 'semgrep passes metadata.rebar_envelope through verbatim' but engine_b.py:302-309 says semgrep does NOT carry custom metadata into SARIF and rebar RE-INJECTS it into rule.properties.rebar_envelope — verify against code, correct the pinned-decision wording) and A19 (verbatim duplicate paragraphs to dedupe)."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782814456655143001,"uuid":"8058b68d-7c79-49a2-983a-ac68ae104daf"}